HEADWORD: Bawcock
<hw>Baw"cock</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From F.
<ets>beau</ets> fine + E. <ets>cock</ets> (the bird); or more prob. fr.
OF. <ets>baud</ets> bold, gay + E. <ets>cock</ets>. Cf.
<er>Bawd</er>.]</ety> <def>A fine fellow; -- a term of endearment.</def>
